race.comment: SHOWTIME CAESAR (1) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 1.1 lengths (19.49) at Q Straight. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Can bounce back. DONE AND DUSTED (7) was sent out long odds last time but charged out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 3 length fourth (19.28) over 350m at Q Straight. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Leading chance. NORTH STAR (6) hit the ground running from a squeeze draw and was prominent throughout but faded out of it when 6th at this track in a Mix 5. Expected to give a good account. FLYING AVOCADO (2) warrants respect although new to this track.
